---
description: Quray project rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Stack: React 19, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS v4. Not Next.js.

Tailwind v4: all theme tokens live in @theme {} in tokens.css. No tailwind.config.ts.
Never hardcode hex colors, font names, px font sizes, or border radii in components.
Use only Tailwind utility classes mapped to CSS variables.

Components: functional, arrow function syntax, named exports only.
Prefer interfaces over types. No enums — use string union types.
No inline styles. No style={{}} attributes.
Check src/components/ui/ before creating new primitives.

Responsive: mobile-first, use best judgment.

## Styleguide upkeep

The /styleguide page (src/pages/Styleguide.tsx) is a living design system reference and a portfolio artifact. Keep it in sync:

- When you create or modify a component in src/components/, update its section in Styleguide.tsx in the SAME change — show the component in all its meaningful states (default, hover, active, disabled, error, etc.).
- When you add a new design token in tokens.css, add its swatch/sample to the matching Foundations section (Colors, Typography, Spacing, Radii).
- When a component gains a new state or variant, add that state to its styleguide section.
- Always render the REAL component, never a copy. Import from src/components/.
- After updating, briefly note in your reply what you added to the styleguide.
